{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849550779,"sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","part":{"id":"prt_d78e1b14f0019k6D7RkAL6Jhz1","messageID":"msg_d78e19cae001RVM6kOUaIPRrCr","sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6551a6303be948919f7e8934e0a415b6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 Spec\n2: \n3: [To be filled]\n\n(End of file - total 3 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 Spec\n\n[To be filled]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/spec.md","time":{"start":1775849550762,"end":1775849550777}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849550782,"sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","part":{"id":"prt_d78e1b38f001OT1znOsS3dXI0h","messageID":"msg_d78e19cae001RVM6kOUaIPRrCr","sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-21d45f9a3af24e429c5ef194ff20424c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 Design - Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The Router module provides HTTP reverse proxy capabilities for routing client requests to sandbox instances (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter). It acts as the entry point for all external traffic, managing session-based routing, authentication, and request forwarding.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Diagram\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────┐\n13: │  Client Request │\n14: └────────┬────────┘\n15:          │\n16:          ▼\n17: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n18: │  HTTP Server (Gin)                  │\n19: │  - Request Validation               │\n20: │  - Concurrency Limiting             │\n21: │  - Logging/Recovery                 │\n22: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n23:          │\n24:          ▼\n25: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n26: │  Router Handler                     │\n27: │  - Session Extraction               │\n28: │  - JWT Generation/Validation        │\n29: │  - Sandbox Lookup                   │\n30: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n31:          │\n32:          ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │  Session Manager                    │\n35: │  - Cache Lookup                     │\n36: │  - Workload Manager Call            │\n37: │  - Session Creation/Retrieval       │\n38: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n39:          │\n40:          ▼\n41: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n42: │  Reverse Proxy                      │\n43: │  - Request Forwarding               │\n44: │  - Response Modification            │\n45: │  - Header Management                │\n46: └────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n47:          │\n48:          ▼\n49: ┌─────────────────┐\n50: │  Sandbox Pod    │\n51: └─────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Layered Architecture\n55: \n56: 1. **HTTP Layer**: Gin-based HTTP server with middleware\n57: 2. **Routing Layer**: Request routing and session management\n58: 3. **Proxy Layer**: HTTP reverse proxy with transport configuration\n59: 4. **Integration Layer**: Store, JWT, and workload manager clients\n60: \n61: ### Key Components\n62: \n63: #### Server (`server.go`)\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type Server struct {\n67:     config         *Config\n68:     engine         *gin.Engine\n69:     httpServer     *http.Server\n70:     sessionManager SessionManager\n71:     storeClient    store.Store\n72:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n73:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: **Responsibilities:**\n78: - HTTP server lifecycle management\n79: - Route registration and middleware setup\n80: - Graceful shutdown handling\n81: - Health check endpoints\n82: \n83: #### Session Manager (`session_manager.go`)\n84: \n85: ```go\n86: type SessionManager interface {\n87:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n88: }\n89: \n90: type manager struct {\n91:     storeClient     store.Store\n92:     workloadMgrAddr string\n93:     httpClient      *http.Client\n94: }\n95: ```\n96: \n97: **Responsibilities:**\n98: - Session-based sandbox lookup\n99: - Cache integration for performance\n100: - Workload manager communication\n101: - Session validation\n102: \n103: #### JWT Manager (`jwt.go`)\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type JWTManager struct {\n107:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n108:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n109:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n110: }\n111: ```\n112: \n113: **Responsibilities:**\n114: - JWT token generation for sandbox authentication\n115: - RSA key pair generation and persistence\n116: - Kubernetes secret management for key storage\n117: - Token-based authentication for sandbox requests\n118: \n119: ## Data Structures\n120: \n121: ### Configuration\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: type Config struct {\n125:     Port                  string\n126:     Debug                 bool\n127:     EnableTLS             bool\n128:     TLSCert               string\n129:     TLSKey                string\n130:     MaxConcurrentRequests int\n131: }\n132: ```\n133: \n134: **Default Values:**\n135: - Port: \"8080\"\n136: - Debug: false\n137: - EnableTLS: false\n138: - TLSCert: \"\"\n139: - TLSKey: \"\"\n140: - MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000\n141: \n142: ### Session Data\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: type SandboxInfo struct {\n146:     Kind             string              // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n147:     SandboxID        string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n148:     SandboxName      string              // Pod name\n149:     SandboxNamespace string              // Pod namespace\n150:     Name             string              // Resource name\n151:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint // Available service endpoints\n152:     SessionID        string              // Session identifier\n153:     CreatedAt        time.Time           // Session creation time\n154:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           // Session expiration time\n155:     Status           string              // Sandbox status\n156:     PodIP            string              // Pod IP address\n157:     WorkloadName     string              // Workload name\n158:     Namespace        string              // Resource namespace\n159:     LastActivityAt   time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### Entry Point\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n167:     Path     string // URL path prefix\n168:     Protocol string // \"http\" or \"https\"\n169:     Endpoint string // Target URL endpoint\n170: }\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### JWT Claims\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type JWTClaims struct {\n177:     SessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n178:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ## API Contracts\n183: \n184: ### HTTP Endpoints\n185: \n186: #### Health Checks\n187: \n188: **GET `/health/live`**\n189: - Purpose: Liveness probe for Kubernetes\n190: - Response: `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n191: - No authentication required\n192: \n193: **GET `/health/ready`**\n194: - Purpose: Readiness probe for Kubernetes\n195: - Response: `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"...\"}`\n196: - Checks session manager availability\n197: \n198: #### Agent Runtime Invocation\n199: \n200: **GET/POST `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`**\n201: \n202: **Middleware:**\n203: 1. `gin.Logger()` - Request logging\n204: 2. `gin.Recovery()` - Panic recovery\n205: 3. `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` - Concurrency control\n206: \n207: **Path Parameters:**\n208: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n209: - `name`: AgentRuntime resource name\n210: - `path`: Request path to forward to sandbox\n211: \n212: **Flow:**\n213: 1. Extract or generate session ID from request\n214: 2. Validate session and retrieve sandbox info\n215: 3. Generate JWT token for authentication\n216: 4. Reverse proxy request to sandbox endpoint\n217: 5. Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n218: \n219: **Success Response:** Proxied sandbox response\n220: \n221: **Error Responses:**\n222: - 400: Invalid request parameters\n223: - 404: Sandbox not found\n224: - 429: Concurrency limit exceeded\n225: - 500: Internal server error\n226: \n227: #### Code Interpreter Invocation\n228: \n229: **GET/POST `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`**\n230: \n231: Same flow and error handling as Agent Runtime invocation.\n232: \n233: ### Workload Manager API\n234: \n235: **Create Sandbox**\n236: - Method: POST\n237: - Endpoint: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime` or `/v1/code-interpreter`\n238: - Request Body: `CreateSandboxRequest`\n239: - Response Body: `CreateSandboxResponse`\n240: \n241: **Get Session**\n242: - Method: GET\n243: - Endpoint: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/session/{sessionID}`\n244: - Response Body: `GetSessionResponse`\n245: \n246: ### Store Interface\n247: \n248: The router uses the `store.Store` interface for caching session data:\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: type Store interface {\n252:     Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, error)\n253:     Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte, ttl time.Duration) error\n254:     Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ## Error Handling\n259: \n260: ### Error Types\n261: \n262: 1. **Validation Errors** (400)\n263:    - Invalid resource kind\n264:    - Missing required parameters\n265:    - Invalid session ID format\n266: \n267: 2. **Not Found Errors** (404)\n268:    - AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource not found\n269:    - Session not found\n270:    - Sandbox pod not available\n271: \n272: 3. **Concurrency Limit Errors** (429)\n273:    - Maximum concurrent requests exceeded\n274:    - Server under heavy load\n275: \n276: 4. **Internal Server Errors** (500)\n277:    - Workload manager communication failures\n278:    - Store access failures\n279:    - Proxy transport errors\n280:    - JWT generation failures\n281: \n282: ### Error Response Format\n283: \n284: ```go\n285: type ErrorResponse struct {\n286:     Error string `json:\"error\"`\n287:     Code  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n288: }\n289: ```\n290: \n291: **Example:**\n292: ```json\n293: {\n294:   \"error\": \"sandbox not found\",\n295:   \"code\": \"SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND\"\n296: }\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Error Handling Strategy\n300: \n301: 1. **Graceful Degradation**\n302:    - Return cached sandbox info if workload manager is temporarily unavailable\n303:    - Continue serving requests during partial failures\n304: \n305: 2. **Circuit Breaker Pattern**\n306:    - Limit retries to workload manager\n307:    - Fail fast after consecutive failures\n308:    - Automatic recovery after timeout\n309: \n310: 3. **Context Cancellation**\n311:    - Propagate context timeouts to downstream calls\n312:    - Clean up resources on cancellation\n313:    - Respect client deadlines\n314: \n315: 4. **Logging**\n316:    - Log all errors with structured fields\n317:    - Include request correlation IDs\n318:    - Aggregate error metrics\n319: \n320: ## Testing Strategy\n321: \n322: ### Unit Tests\n323: \n324: #### Server Tests\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: func TestNewServer(t *testing.T)\n328: func TestServer_Start(t *testing.T)\n329: func TestServer_Shutdown(t *testing.T)\n330: ```\n331: \n332: **Coverage:**\n333: - Server initialization\n334: - Graceful shutdown\n335: - Configuration validation\n336: \n337: #### Session Manager Tests\n338: \n339: ```go\n340: func TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession(t *testing.T)\n341: func TestSessionManager_cacheHit(t *testing.T)\n342: func TestSessionManager_cacheMiss(t *testing.T)\n343: func TestSessionManager_workloadManagerCall(t *testing.T)\n344: ```\n345: \n346: **Coverage:**\n347: - Cache hit scenarios\n348: - Cache miss scenarios\n349: - Workload manager communication\n350: - Error handling\n351: \n352: #### JWT Manager Tests\n353: \n354: ```go\n355: func TestJWTManager_GenerateToken(t *testing.T)\n356: func TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(t *testing.T)\n357: func TestJWTManager_keyRotation(t *testing.T)\n358: ```\n359: \n360: **Coverage:**\n361: - Token generation and validation\n362: - RSA key generation\n363: - Secret persistence\n364: - Key rotation scenarios\n365: \n366: #### Handler Tests\n367: \n368: ```go\n369: func TestHandleHealthLive(t *testing.T)\n370: func TestHandleHealthReady(t *testing.T)\n371: func TestHandleAgentInvoke(t *testing.T)\n372: func TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke(t *testing.T)\n373: ```\n374: \n375: **Coverage:**\n376: - Request handling\n377: - Parameter extraction\n378: - Response formatting\n379: - Error cases\n380: \n381: #### Middleware Tests\n382: \n383: ```go\n384: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(t *testing.T)\n385: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_exceeded(t *testing.T)\n386: ```\n387: \n388: **Coverage:**\n389: - Concurrency control\n390: - Rate limiting\n391: - Headers and status codes\n392: \n393: #### Proxy Tests\n394: \n395: ```go\n396: func TestReverseProxy_Forwarding(t *testing.T)\n397: func TestReverseProxy_HeaderModification(t *testing.T)\n398: func TestReverseProxy_Transport(t *testing.T)\n399: ```\n400: \n401: **Coverage:**\n402: - Request forwarding\n403: - Header manipulation\n404: - Response modification\n405: - Transport configuration\n406: \n407: ### Integration Tests\n408: \n409: #### End-to-End Tests\n410: \n411: ```go\n412: func TestE2E_AgentRuntimeInvocation(t *testing.T)\n413: func TestE2E_CodeInterpreterInvocation(t *testing.T)\n414: func TestE2E_SessionLifecycle(t *testing.T)\n415: func TestE2E_ErrorScenarios(t *testing.T)\n416: ```\n417: \n418: **Setup:**\n419: - Mock workload manager server\n420: - In-memory store\n421: - Test AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n422: \n423: **Coverage:**\n424: - Complete request flow\n425: - Session creation and reuse\n426: - Error propagation\n427: - Performance characteristics\n428: \n429: #### Store Integration Tests\n430: \n431: ```go\n432: func TestStoreIntegration_SessionCaching(t *testing.T)\n433: func TestStoreIntegration_TTLExpiration(t *testing.T)\n434: ```\n435: \n436: **Coverage:**\n437: - Store operations\n438: - TTL behavior\n439: - Concurrent access\n440: \n441: ### Performance Tests\n442: \n443: ```go\n444: func BenchmarkHandleAgentInvoke(b *testing.B)\n445: func BenchmarkHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke(b *testing.B)\n446: func BenchmarkConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(b *testing.B)\n447: func BenchmarkReverseProxy(b *testing.B)\n448: ```\n449: \n450: **Metrics:**\n451: - Request throughput\n452: - Latency percentiles\n453: - Memory usage\n454: - Goroutine count\n455: \n456: ### Load Tests\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: func TestLoad_ConcurrentRequests(t *testing.T)\n460: func TestLoad_LongRunningRequests(t *testing.T)\n461: func TestLoad_MixedWorkload(t *testing.T)\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **Scenarios:**\n465: - Concurrent request handling\n466: - Memory pressure\n467: - Connection pooling\n468: - Backlog management\n469: \n470: ### Security Tests\n471: \n472: ```go\n473: func TestSecurity_JWTValidation(t *testing.T)\n474: func TestSecurity_PathTraversal(t *testing.T)\n475: func TestSecurity_HeaderInjection(t *testing.T)\n476: func TestSecurity_TLSConfiguration(t *testing.T)\n477: ```\n478: \n479: **Coverage:**\n480: - Authentication bypass attempts\n481: - Input validation\n482: - Header manipulation\n483: - TLS certificate handling\n484: \n485: ## Security Considerations\n486: \n487: ### Authentication\n488: \n489: 1. **JWT-based Authentication**\n490:    - RSA 2048-bit keys\n491:    - RS256 signing algorithm\n492:    - 5-minute token expiration\n493:    - Key rotation support\n494: \n495: 2. **Secret Management**\n496:    - Kubernetes secrets for key storage\n497:    - In-cluster service account tokens\n498:    - Secure key generation\n499: \n500: ### Authorization\n501: \n502: 1. **Namespace Isolation**\n503:    - Requests scoped to specific namespace\n504:    - Cross-namespace access prevention\n505: \n506: 2. **Resource Access Control**\n507:    - Resource name validation\n508:    - Kind-based routing\n509: \n510: ### Transport Security\n511: \n512: 1. **TLS Support**\n513:    - Optional TLS termination\n514:    - Certificate validation\n515:    - Secure cipher suites\n516: \n517: 2. **HTTP/2 Support**\n518:    - HTTP/2 transport configuration\n519:    - Connection pooling\n520:    - Multiplexing\n521: \n522: ### Input Validation\n523: \n524: 1. **Path Sanitization**\n525:    - Path traversal prevention\n526:    - URL normalization\n527:    - Reserved path handling\n528: \n529: 2. **Parameter Validation**\n530:    - Namespace validation\n531:    - Resource name validation\n532:    - Session ID validation\n533: \n534: ### Rate Limiting\n535: \n536: 1. **Concurrency Control**\n537:    - Configurable concurrency limits\n538:    - 429 responses on limit exceeded\n539:    - Backpressure management\n540: \n541: ## Performance Optimizations\n542: \n543: ### Caching\n544: \n545: 1. **Session Caching**\n546:    - Store-based cache\n547:    - Configurable TTL\n548:    - Cache invalidation\n549: \n550: 2. **Connection Pooling**\n551:    - HTTP/2 transport\n552:    - Keep-alive connections\n553:    - Connection reuse\n554: \n555: ### Request Processing\n556: \n557: 1. **Streaming**\n558:    - Response streaming\n559:    - Chunked encoding\n560:    - No buffering\n561: \n562: 2. **Zero-Copy**\n563:    - Efficient proxy forwarding\n564:    - Minimal request modification\n565:    - Low overhead\n566: \n567: ### Resource Management\n568: \n569: 1. **Goroutine Pooling**\n570:    - Bounded concurrency\n571:    - Worker pool pattern\n572:    - Context cancellation\n573: \n574: 2. **Memory Management**\n575:    - Buffer pooling\n576:    - Memory reuse\n577:    - Garbage collection optimization\n578: \n579: ## Monitoring and Observability\n580: \n581: ### Metrics\n582: \n583: 1. **HTTP Metrics**\n584:    - Request count\n585:    - Response time\n586:    - Error rate\n587:    - Active connections\n588: \n589: 2. **Proxy Metrics**\n590:    - Proxy requests\n591:    - Backend latency\n592:    - Proxy errors\n593: \n594: 3. **Session Metrics**\n595:    - Active sessions\n596:    - Cache hits/misses\n597:    - Session creation rate\n598: \n599: ### Logging\n600: \n601: 1. **Structured Logging**\n602:    - Request correlation IDs\n603:    - Session IDs\n604:    - Error stack traces\n605:    - Performance data\n606: \n607: 2. **Log Levels**\n608:    - Debug: Detailed request/response\n609:    - Info: Key events and errors\n610:    - Error: Failure conditions\n611:    - Fatal: Critical failures\n612: \n613: ### Tracing\n614: \n615: 1. **Distributed Tracing**\n616:    - Request tracing\n617:    - Span propagation\n618:    - Performance profiling\n619: \n620: ### Health Checks\n621: \n622: 1. **Liveness Probe**\n623:    - HTTP endpoint `/health/live`\n624:    - Basic server health\n625: \n626: 2. **Readiness Probe**\n627:    - HTTP endpoint `/health/ready`\n628:    - Dependency health checks\n629: \n630: ## Deployment\n631: \n632: ### Configuration\n633: \n634: **Environment Variables:**\n635: - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`: Workload manager endpoint (required)\n636: - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`: Router namespace (default: `default`)\n637: \n638: **CLI Flags:**\n639: - `-port`: Server port (default: 8080)\n640: - `-enable-tls`: Enable TLS (default: false)\n641: - `-tls-cert`: TLS certificate path\n642: - `-tls-key`: TLS key path\n643: - `-debug`: Debug mode (default: false)\n644: - `-max-concurrent-requests`: Max concurrent requests (default: 1000)\n645: \n646: ### Kubernetes Deployment\n647: \n648: **Deployment Manifest:**\n649: ```yaml\n650: apiVersion: apps/v1\n651: kind: Deployment\n652: metadata:\n653:   name: agentcube-router\n654: spec:\n655:   replicas: 3\n656:   selector:\n657:     matchLabels:\n658:       app: agentcube-router\n659:   template:\n660:     metadata:\n661:       labels:\n662:         app: agentcube-router\n663:     spec:\n664:       containers:\n665:       - name: router\n666:         image: volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest\n667:         ports:\n668:         - containerPort: 8080\n669:         env:\n670:         - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n671:           value: \"http://agentcube-workload-manager:8081\"\n672:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n673:           value: \"default\"\n674:         livenessProbe:\n675:           httpGet:\n676:             path: /health/live\n677:             port: 8080\n678:         readinessProbe:\n679:           httpGet:\n680:             path: /health/ready\n681:             port: 8080\n682: ```\n683: \n684: **Service Manifest:**\n685: ```yaml\n686: apiVersion: v1\n687: kind: Service\n688: metadata:\n689:   name: agentcube-router\n690: spec:\n691:   selector:\n692:     app: agentcube-router\n693:   ports:\n694:   - port: 80\n695:     targetPort: 8080\n696:   type: LoadBalancer\n697: ```\n698: \n699: ### Scalability\n700: \n701: 1. **Horizontal Scaling**\n702:    - Stateless design\n703:    - Shared session store\n704:    - Load balancer distribution\n705: \n706: 2. **Vertical Scaling**\n707:    - Configurable concurrency limits\n708:    - Resource requests/limits\n709:    - Performance tuning\n710: \n711: ## Future Enhancements\n712: \n713: 1. **WebSocket Support**\n714:    - Real-time communication\n715:    - Connection upgrades\n716:    - Session management\n717: \n718: 2. **Advanced Routing**\n719:    - Weight-based routing\n720:    - A/B testing\n721:    - Canary deployments\n722: \n723: 3. **Security Enhancements**\n724:    - Mutual TLS\n725:    - IP whitelisting\n726:    - Rate limiting per client\n727: \n728: 4. **Performance Improvements**\n729:    - HTTP/3 support\n730:    - QUIC protocol\n731:    - Compression\n732: \n733: 5. **Observability**\n734:    - Prometheus metrics\n735:    - Grafana dashboards\n736:    - Alerting rules\n737: \n738: ## Dependencies\n739: \n740: ### Runtime Dependencies\n741: \n742: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`: HTTP framework\n743: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`: JWT library\n744: - `golang.org/x/net/http2`: HTTP/2 support\n745: - `k8s.io/client-go`: Kubernetes client\n746: - `k8s.io/klog/v2`: Logging\n747: \n748: ### Internal Dependencies\n749: \n750: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`: Store interface\n751: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`: Common types\n752: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`: API types\n753: \n754: ## References\n755: \n756: - [Gin Framework Documentation](https://gin-gonic.com/docs/)\n757: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n758: - [HTTP Reverse Proxy Design](https://github.com/golang/go/tree/master/src/net/http/httputil)\n759: - [JWT Best Practices](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8725)\n\n(End of file - total 759 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 Design - Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Router module provides HTTP reverse proxy capabilities for routing client requests to sandbox instances (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter). It acts as the entry point for all external traffic, managing session-based routing, authentication, and request forwarding.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  Client Request │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  HTTP Server (Gin)                  │\n│  - Request Validation               │\n│  - Concurrency Limiting             │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775849550765,"end":1775849550779}}}}
