{"type":"text","timestamp":1775849617112,"sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","part":{"id":"prt_d78e270cb0011oZi6vB3xhRHlC","messageID":"msg_d78e2614c00139VL35CpassS7V","sessionID":"ses_2871ec0bbffeG75S7Y1zWrjj42","type":"text","text":"## Verification Report for AR-009 — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n### Spec Discrepancy\n\nThe spec you provided describes a **Kubernetes client-go library** for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, but the actual implementation is the **Router HTTP reverse proxy core**. These are different components.\n\n### Router Implementation Verification\n\nBased on the actual router design spec (`changes/AR-009/design.md`), here's the verification status:\n\n#### ✅ Core Components Implemented\n\n**Server (`server.go`)**\n- ✅ HTTP server lifecycle management with graceful shutdown\n- ✅ Route registration for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocations\n- ✅ Health check endpoints: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`\n- ✅ TLS support with configurable certificates\n\n**Session Manager (`session_manager.go`)**\n- ✅ Session-based sandbox lookup with caching\n- ✅ Workload manager API integration\n- ✅ Cache hit/miss logic using store interface\n\n**JWT Manager (`jwt.go`)**\n- ✅ JWT token generation with 5-minute expiration\n- ✅ RSA 2048-bit key pair generation\n- ✅ Kubernetes secret management for key storage\n- ✅ RS256 signing algorithm\n\n**Reverse Proxy (`proxy.go`)**\n- ✅ HTTP reverse proxy with JWT authentication\n- ✅ Header modification (forwarding, X-Forwarded-* headers)\n- ✅ HTTP/2 transport configuration with connection pooling\n- ✅ Response streaming without buffering\n\n**Middleware (`middleware.go`)**\n- ✅ Concurrency limiting with semaphore (configurable max concurrent requests)\n- ✅ Request/response logging with correlation IDs\n- ✅ Panic recovery with error responses\n- ✅ Metrics tracking (request count, response time, active connections)\n\n**Handlers (`handlers.go`)**\n- ✅ `GET /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`\n- ✅ `GET /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`\n- ✅ Session ID extraction and generation\n- ✅ Namespace and resource name validation\n\n**Configuration (`config.go`)**\n- ✅ Environment variable loading\n- ✅ Validation logic with appropriate defaults\n- ✅ Configurable timeouts (read, write, idle)\n\n**Error Handling (`errors.go`)**\n- ✅ Custom error types with HTTP status codes\n- ✅ Error response formatting with error codes\n- ✅ `SandboxNotFoundError`, `SessionExpiredError`, `WorkloadManagerError`, `ValidationError`\n\n**Utilities (`utils.go`)**\n- ✅ Namespace and resource name validation (Kubernetes-compliant)\n- ✅ Path sanitization (prevents path traversal)\n- ✅ Session ID parsing (UUID format)\n- ✅ Entry point matching logic\n\n#### ✅ Test Results\n\n```\n=== All tests passed ===\nok  github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router  (cached)\n```\n\nTest coverage: **12.3%** (below target of 80%)\n\n#### ✅ Code Quality\n\n```bash\ngo vet ./pkg/router/...  # ✅ No warnings\ngo build ./pkg/router/...  # ✅ Compiles successfully\n```\n\n### Missing Components\n\n#### ❌ Client-go Library\n\nThe spec describes a generated Kubernetes client library that should provide:\n\n```go\n// Expected but NOT found:\n// - github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n// - Clientset with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n// - AgentRuntimesGetter with CRUD operations\n// - CodeInterpretersGetter with CRUD operations\n```\n\n### Implementation Tasks Status (from tasks.md)\n\n| Task | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| Task 1: Package structure | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 2: Configuration | ✅ Complete with tests |\n| Task 3: Types and data structures | ✅ Complete with tests |\n| Task 4: JWT manager | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 5: Session manager | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 6: Reverse proxy | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 7: Middleware | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 8: HTTP handlers | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 9: HTTP server | ✅ Complete |\n| Task 10: Error handling | ✅ Complete with tests |\n| Task 11: Integration tests | ⚠️ Not found (e2e tests missing) |\n| Task 12: Performance tests | ⚠️ Not found (benchmarks missing) |\n| Task 13: Security tests | ⚠️ Not found (security tests missing) |\n| Task 14: Documentation | ⚠️ README missing, doc.go minimal |\n| Task 15: Final verification | ⚠️ Coverage too low |\n\n### Summary\n\n**Router Implementation**: ✅ Core functionality complete and working\n- All required components implemented\n- Tests pass\n- Code compiles without warnings\n\n**Client-go Library**: ❌ Not implemented\n- This is a separate component not present in the current codebase\n\n**Gaps**:\n- Low test coverage (12.3% vs target 80%)\n- Missing integration tests\n- Missing performance benchmarks\n- Missing security tests\n- Missing comprehensive documentation","time":{"start":1775849617109,"end":1775849617109}}}
